---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us" 
  description="Learn about Noda Ueki and Bonsai's commitment to authentic Japanese landscaping traditions and our expertise in Ueki and Bonsai services."
>
  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1604608672516-f1b6123627b7?w=1920&q=80');">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1>About Noda Ueki and Bonsai</h1>
      <p>Honoring tradition, cultivating beauty</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Story -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div>
          <h2>Our Story</h2>
          <p>Noda Ueki and Bonsai was founded on a deep respect for the centuries-old traditions of Japanese horticulture and a passion for sharing these timeless practices with the Pacific Northwest community.</p>
          
          <p>Having trained under master gardeners in Japan and studied the classical texts on garden design and tree cultivation, we bring authentic expertise to every project. Yet we're not merely preservationists - we thoughtfully adapt traditional techniques to work harmoniously with our unique climate, native species, and modern lifestyles.</p>
          
          <p>What began as a personal journey to understand the philosophical and practical aspects of Japanese gardening has evolved into a practice dedicated to creating spaces of tranquility and beauty for our clients. Each garden we design, each tree we shape, and each Bonsai we cultivate represents a bridge between ancient wisdom and contemporary life.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="about-image">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1585320806297-9794b3e4eeae?w=800&q=80" alt="Skilled hands pruning a Japanese pine tree" />
          <p class="image-caption">Traditional Niwaki pruning technique on Japanese black pine</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Approach -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center">Our Approach</h2>
      
      <div class="approach-grid">
        <div class="approach-item">
          <div class="approach-number">01</div>
          <h3>Deep Listening</h3>
          <p>We begin every project by truly understanding your vision, your space, and your relationship with nature. Your goals and dreams guide our design.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="approach-item">
          <div class="approach-number">02</div>
          <h3>Authentic Techniques</h3>
          <p>We employ traditional Japanese methods - from site assessment principles to pruning techniques - that have been refined over centuries.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="approach-item">
          <div class="approach-number">03</div>
          <h3>Site Harmony</h3>
          <p>Every location is unique. We work with your specific conditions - sun, shade, drainage, views - to create a design that feels inevitable and natural.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="approach-item">
          <div class="approach-number">04</div>
          <h3>Seasonal Perspective</h3>
          <p>Japanese gardens reveal different beauties through the seasons. We design with the full annual cycle in mind, ensuring year-round interest.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="approach-item">
          <div class="approach-number">05</div>
          <h3>Living Relationships</h3>
          <p>A garden is not a static installation but a living ecosystem. We provide guidance for ongoing care so your garden matures beautifully over time.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="approach-item">
          <div class="approach-number">06</div>
          <h3>Cultural Respect</h3>
          <p>We honor the deep cultural heritage of Japanese garden arts, avoiding superficial "zen" aesthetics in favor of thoughtful, meaningful design.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="philosophy-section">
        <h2>Design Philosophy</h2>
        <p class="lead">Our work is guided by the seven principles of Japanese aesthetics, adapted from Zen Buddhist philosophy:</p>
        
        <div class="principles-list">
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Fukinsei (不均斉) - Asymmetry</h3>
            <p>True beauty lies in natural, asymmetric balance rather than rigid symmetry. We create compositions that feel balanced yet dynamic.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Kanso (簡素) - Simplicity</h3>
            <p>Restraint and clarity. We edit ruthlessly, ensuring every element has purpose and nothing feels cluttered or excessive.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Shizen (自然) - Naturalness</h3>
            <p>Effortless beauty that appears unforced. Our designs and pruning work with the natural growth patterns of plants rather than against them.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Yugen (幽玄) - Subtle Depth</h3>
            <p>The beauty of mystery and suggestion. Gardens should reveal themselves slowly, inviting exploration and contemplation.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Datsuzoku (脱俗) - Freedom from Convention</h3>
            <p>Creativity within tradition. While we honor classical forms, we're not bound by rigid rules - each garden is unique to its place and people.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Seijaku (静寂) - Tranquility</h3>
            <p>Peace and energized calm. Our gardens provide respite from busy modern life, creating spaces for reflection and renewal.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h3>Wabi-Sabi (侘寂) - Imperfect Beauty</h3>
            <p>Finding beauty in impermanence, imperfection, and incompleteness. Weathered stones, moss, and the natural aging of materials add character.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Service Area -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-area-content">
        <h2>Service Area</h2>
        <p>We're proud to serve the greater Portland, Oregon metropolitan area and surrounding regions. Our primary service area includes:</p>
        
        <div class="locations-grid">
          <div class="location-group">
            <h3>Oregon</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Portland metro (Multnomah County)</li>
              <li>Beaverton, Hillsboro (Washington County)</li>
              <li>Lake Oswego, Oregon City (Clackamas County)</li>
              <li>Salem</li>
              <li>Eugene</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="location-group">
            <h3>Washington</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Vancouver</li>
              <li>Camas</li>
              <li>Battle Ground</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p>For larger projects or special circumstances, we may be able to travel to other Pacific Northwest locations. Please inquire about your specific location.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>Let's Create Something Beautiful Together</h2>
      <p>Schedule a consultation to discuss your vision and explore possibilities for your space.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    height: 50vh;
    min-height: 400px;
  }
  
  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }
  
  .about-image {
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;
  }
  
  .about-image img {
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .image-caption {
    font-size: var(--font-size-small);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  
  .approach-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
  }
  
  .approach-item {
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .approach-number {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .approach-item h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-quote);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }
  
  .principles-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
  }
  
  .principle-item h3 {
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }
  
  .locations-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
  }
  
  .location-group h3 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .location-group ul {
    list-style: none;
  }
  
  .location-group li {
    padding: var(--spacing-xs) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #E0E0E0;
  }
  
  .location-group li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, #1e3829 100%);
    color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }
  
  .cta-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .cta-section p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-quote);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .approach-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .content-grid,
    .approach-grid,
    .locations-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    
    .about-image {
      position: static;
    }
  }
</style>

